---
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import FormattedDate from '../components/FormattedDate.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const allPosts = await getCollection('blog');

// Show the first post from each core series in the home page article section.
const featuredSlugs = [
  'training-the-mind/attention-control-theory',
  'gael-performance-toolkit/gael-performance-toolkit',
];

const latestPosts = featuredSlugs
  .map((slug) => allPosts.find((post) => post.slug === slug))
  .filter((post): post is (typeof allPosts)[number] => post !== undefined);
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
  </head>
  <body class="home-page">
    <Header />
    <main class="container">
      <section class="hero">
        <h1>About Me</h1>
      </section>

      <section class="intro about-grid">
        <div class="about-text">
          <p>My name is Emily Phelan, I am a 32-year-old female athlete living in London, and I play Ladies Gaelic Football.</p>
          <p>Sport has always been a huge part of my life, but my journey with it hasn't always been straightforward. I've experienced anxiety and depression throughout my sporting career, and for a long time I didn't really have the language or the tools to understand what was happening in my own head.</p>
          <p>I didn't understand why pressure felt like too much sometimes. I didn't understand why my confidence could swing so much. I didn't understand why certain moments affected me so much more then others. I just knew I loved the sport, but I was also struggling in it.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="arrow-image-row arrow-image-row-reverse">
          <img class="about-image-img" src="/EmilyPhelan-Depressed.jpg" alt="Emily Phelan" />
          <span class="arrow-to-image" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="60" height="24" viewBox="0 0 60 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <path d="M60 12H10m0 0l8-8m-8 8l8 8" stroke="var(--green-lime)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div class="guess-arrow-text">
            <p>Number 18 is me on league final day. I remember feeling happy for my team, but I couldn't fully feel it for myself because I was so caught up in my own performance. I wasn't in a good place mentally, and that showed on the pitch.</p>
            <p>But what I understand now, looking back, is that it wasn't just performance anxiety. I was dealing with undiagnosed anxiety and depression at the time, and that naturally spilled over into my sport.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="about-text">
          <p>I just knew that everything felt heavier than it should have, not just games, but life in general. There were days I struggled to get out of bed, times I would feel really low for no clear reason, and moments where I experienced panic attacks that I didn't fully understand at the time.</p>
          <p>And one of those panic attacks actually happened that day, when I should have been happy and celebrating with my teammates. Instead, I was completely overwhelmed in my own head. My mind was constantly busy. I didn't really know how to separate what was going on internally from how I was performing externally and the celebrations going on around me afterwards.</p>
          <p>I was overthinking, second-guessing myself, and never really fully present in the moment. And afterwards, I remember replaying everything in my head over and over, feeling really disconnected from what had just happened, like I wasn't even fully in it in the first place.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="arrow-image-row">
          <div class="guess-arrow-text">
            <p>And then there's me a year later on the exact same league final day. Same pitch. Same occasion. But a completely different headspace.</p>
            <p>We actually lost the final that day, but my experience of it was completely different.</p>
            <p>I was calm. I was present. And I felt content within myself, regardless of the result. I could take the game for what it was, without it defining how I felt about myself afterwards.</p>
            <p>That didn't happen overnight. It took a lot of work on my mental health, a lot of learning, and a lot of uncomfortable reflection about how I was thinking, feeling, and showing up in both life and sport.</p>
            <p>The road between those two versions of me was long. And it wasn't linear. But it was worth it.</p>
          </div>
          <span class="arrow-to-image" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg width="60" height="24" viewBox="0 0 60 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <path d="M0 12h50m0 0l-8-8m8 8l-8 8" stroke="var(--green-lime)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg>
          </span>
          <img class="about-image-img" src="/assets/saoirse.png" alt="Emily Phelan" />
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="hero why-hero">
        <h1>Why Mind the Gael Exists</h1>
      </section>

      <section class="intro about-grid why-grid">
        <div class="about-text">
          <p>Mind the Gael came from my own journey of trying to understand what was going on in my mind, both in life and in sport.</p>
          <p>And that's really what this platform is now. I'm taking everyone with me on that journey.</p>
          <p>I'm going to continue learning, researching, and exploring psychological concepts around performance, anxiety, attention, and wellbeing. I'll then be breaking it all down in a way that we can actually understand and use.</p>
          <p>Not academic jargon. Not complicated theories that don't translate onto a pitch. Just real, relatable understanding of how your mind works when you're under pressure, when you're doubting yourself, when you're performing, and when things don't go to plan.</p>
          <p>Because I've learned that when you understand your mind, you don't feel as lost in it anymore.</p>
          <p>And that's what Mind the Gael is about, creating a community, learning together, and making mental wellbeing usable in real sport and real life.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="latest-blog-box">
        <h2>Latest Articles</h2>
        <ul class="latest-posts">
          {latestPosts.map((post) => (
            <li>
              <a href={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}>
                <h3>{post.data.title}</h3>
                <p class="post-date">
                  <FormattedDate date={post.data.pubDate} />
                </p>
                {post.data.description && <p class="post-description">{post.data.description}</p>}
              </a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
        <a href="/blog" class="view-all-link">View All Articles →</a>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .hero h1 {
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .hero:not(.why-hero) h1 {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .tagline {
    color: var(--green-light);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .intro p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .why-grid {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-text {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .about-text p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .arrow-image-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .guess-arrow-text {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .arrow-to-image {
    display: inline-block;
    vertical-align: middle;
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
  }

  .arrow-image-row-reverse {
    flex-direction: row;
    justify-content: flex-start;
  }

  .why-hero {
    margin-top: -1rem;
  }

  .about-image-img {
    width: 500px;
    object-fit: cover;
    max-width: 100%;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 2px solid var(--green-lime);
    box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
    display: block;
  }

  .section-heading {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    color: var(--green-lime);
    font-size: 1.7rem;
  }

  .two-col-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .two-col-grid > section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: stretch;
    height: 100%;
  }

  .individual-subscription,
  .team-subscription {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    background-color: rgba(240, 205, 255, 0.1);
    border: 2px solid var(--green-lime);
    border-radius: 8px;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
    height: 100%;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .individual-subscription:hover,
  .team-subscription:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: var(--purple-light);
  }

  .team-contact-form,
  .subscription-form {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: auto;
  }

  .team-contact-form input,
  .subscription-form input {
    padding: 0.75rem;
    border: 2px solid var(--green-lime);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: var(--green-dark);
    color: var(--green-light);
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .team-contact-form input::placeholder,
  .subscription-form input::placeholder {
    color: rgba(244, 255, 232, 0.6);
  }

  .team-contact-form button,
  .subscription-form button {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    background-color: var(--green-lime);
    color: var(--green-dark);
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background-color 0.2s ease;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .team-contact-form button:hover,
  .subscription-form button:hover {
    background-color: var(--purple-light);
  }

  .personal-training-box {
    margin: 0 0 2rem 0;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    background-color: rgba(240, 205, 255, 0.1);
    border: 2px solid var(--green-lime);
    border-radius: 8px;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .personal-training-box:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: var(--purple-light);
  }

  .latest-blog-box {
    background-color: rgba(240, 205, 255, 0.1);
    border: 2px solid var(--green-lime);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 2rem;
    transition: transform 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .latest-blog-box:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: var(--purple-light);
  }

  .latest-posts {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .latest-posts li {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(192, 254, 113, 0.2);
  }

  .latest-posts li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    padding-bottom: 0;
  }

  .latest-posts li a {
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    display: block;
  }

  .latest-posts li a:hover h3 {
    color: var(--purple-light);
  }

  .post-date {
    color: var(--green-light);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .post-description {
    color: var(--green-light);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .view-all-link {
    display: inline-block;
    color: var(--green-lime);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    align-self: center;
  }

  .view-all-link:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--green-lime);
  }

  .coming-soon {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    align-self: center;
  }

  .coming-soon-img {
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    opacity: 0.8;
  }

  .coming-soon-text {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--green-lime);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .two-col-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.25rem;
    }

    .individual-subscription,
    .team-subscription,
    .personal-training-box,
    .latest-blog-box {
      padding: 1.25rem 1rem;
    }

    .section-heading {
      font-size: 1.45rem;
      margin-top: 2.2rem;
    }

    .about-grid {
      max-width: 100%;
    }

    .arrow-image-row,
    .arrow-image-row-reverse {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: 1rem;
    }

    .about-image-img {
      width: min(100%, 360px);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .intro p,
    .guess-arrow-text {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
  }
</style>
